{"ts": "2026-06-09T18:00:35.660848+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 377, "prompt_tokens": 9771, "total_tokens": 10148, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 17, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 9280}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "ddfad9c4594349c7b617808a4cf45d2d", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead8a-e95a-77e1-aeec-fae6d6045cde-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T11_R01", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Thanks for the report, @BruceKZ! I've reviewed the issue against the current codebase and can confirm this is a valid bug.\n\n**Verified:** `scripts/apply_migrations.sh` currently relies on bare shell glob ordering:\n\n```bash\nfor f in migrations/*.sql; do\n```\n\nAnd the migration files have a strict dependency chain:\n1. `001_create_users.sql`\n2. `002_create_sessions.sql` (depends on `users` table existing)\n3. `003_add_session_index.sql` (depends on `sessions` table existing)\n\nOn case-insensitive filesystems (like APFS on macOS) or with non-C locale collation, glob expansion order is not guaranteed to be lexicographic, so `003_` could indeed be applied before `002_`, causing the `psql: relation \"sessions\" does not exist` error.\n\n**Suggested fix** — the most robust approach is to force the locale for the glob expansion while avoiding the pitfalls of parsing `ls`:\n\n```bash\nLC_COLLATE=C\nfor f in migrations/*.sql; do\n```\n\nThis ensures consistent byte-order sorting across all platforms without introducing the edge cases that come with `$(ls ... | sort)` (e.g., filenames with spaces or special characters).\n\nSetting `LC_COLLATE=C` at the top of the script (after the shebang) is a minimal, safe change. A PR would be welcome!"}, "id": "call_70257ce6364c4e3fbfa3f332", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9771, "output_tokens": 377, "total_tokens": 10148, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 9280}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 17}}}}]}}}
