{"ts": "2026-06-09T18:00:43.957568+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:VJEidW | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 9a7ab4a43b359ce089e5b88c4f6f7515daa7431c)", "id": "lc_5489eac9-d665-4d5f-95b3-de711fe66144"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:VJEidW | CREATE TABLE sessions (\n| MCP:VJEidW |     id          UUID PRIMARY KEY,\n| MCP:VJEidW |     user_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n| MCP:VJEidW |     issued_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n| MCP:VJEidW |     expires_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL\n| MCP:VJEidW | );", "id": "lc_3f47c32e-fee0-422d-957d-eabf3fb8a60a"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "273a84c6-0786-4498-9b7f-2c4fa6805bb5", "tool_call_id": "call_286109ccf5194932be87509a", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T18:00:43.966016+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:VJEidW | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 6c708c510171c17fee8c35ed6c39e513620500b8)", "id": "lc_4caa6051-19ba-4447-9af0-a22b487f47ba"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:VJEidW | CREATE INDEX idx_sessions_user_id ON sessions(user_id);", "id": "lc_cc7c679f-4b03-4e94-9188-9f8255d0f511"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "2626d4b1-d515-4ab0-b8c0-e2f239542910", "tool_call_id": "call_d964a36c29854ecf80587992", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T18:01:04.663656+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I'm unable to comment or modify the issue due to token permission restrictions (403 on write operations). However, here is my full triage assessment:\n\n---\n\n## Triage: Issue #1 — `apply_migrations.sh` applies files in wrong order on case-folding filesystems\n\n### Verdict: **Valid bug — confirmed against current codebase**\n\n### Evidence\n\n1. **The script** (`scripts/apply_migrations.sh`) uses a bare glob loop:\n   ```bash\n   for f in migrations/*.sql; do\n   ```\n   It explicitly acknowledges this in a comment: *\"relies on shell glob expansion ordering, not on `find`.\"*\n\n2. **The migration files have a strict dependency chain:**\n   - `001_create_users.sql` — creates the `users` table\n   - `002_create_sessions.sql` — creates `sessions` table with `REFERENCES users(id)`\n   - `003_add_session_index.sql` — `CREATE INDEX idx_sessions_user_id ON sessions(user_id)`\n\n   If `003` runs before `002`, `psql` will correctly error: `relation \"sessions\" does not exist`.\n\n3. **Root cause is real:** Shell glob expansion order depends on the filesystem's collation behavior. On case-insensitive filesystems (APFS on macOS) or with non-C `LC_COLLATE` locales, the sort order is not guaranteed to be lexicographic.\n\n### Recommended Action\n\nThe fix is minimal: add `LC_COLLATE=C` near the top of the script (after the shebang and `set -euo pipefail`) to force byte-order sorting of the glob. This is safer than the reporter's `$(ls ... | sort)` workaround, which can break on filenames with spaces or special characters.\n\n### Issue Status\n\nThe issue should remain **open** and accepted. I was unable to add a comment or label due to the repository token lacking write permissions, but the issue is a valid, confirmed bug.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 542, "prompt_tokens": 10634, "total_tokens": 11176, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 123, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 10176}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "71955a0d29a74a2cb87229010994392e", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead8b-3cbf-7550-8817-c0e3ac8dc0a4-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10634, "output_tokens": 542, "total_tokens": 11176, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 10176}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 123}}}}]}}}
